
[1]boat

   BOAT, n.

   1. A small open vessel, or water craft, usually moved by oars, or
   rowing. The forms, dimensions and uses of boats are very various, and
   some of them carry a light sail. The different kinds of boats have
   different names, as, long-boat,lanch, barge, pinnace,jolly-boat,
   cutter, yawl, ferry-boat, wherry, Moses-boat, punt, felucca,
   fishing-boat,perogue, &c.

   2. A small vessel carrying a mast and sails; but usually described by
   another word, as a packet-boat, passage-boat, advice-boat. &c.

     BOAT, v.t. To transport in a boat; as, to boat goods across a lake.
     __________________________________________________________________

